### ||| AUTO 18 - وعن أبي عبد الرحمن عبد الله بن عمر بن الخطاب رضي الله
~~عنه عن النبي صلى الله عليه وسلم قال : [ إن الله عز وجل يقبل توبة العبد
~~ما لم يغرغر ] رواه الترمذي وقال حديث حسن.
# `18- Abdullah bin `Umar bin Al-Khattab (May Allah be pleased with
~~them) reported that: The Prophet (PBUH) said, "Allah accepts a slave's
~~repentance as long as the latter is not on his death bed (that is,
~~before the soul of the dying person reaches the throat)".
# [At-Tirmidhi, who categorised it as Hadith Hasan].
# Commentary: The word Ghargharah means the stage when soul is about to
~~leave the body and reaches the throat. In other words, the time when one
~~suffers the agony of death.
# Hadith Hasan means that Hadith the authenticity of which is connected
~~without any technical defect. Their narrators, however, are next to
~~those of Hadith Sahih. In the opinion of Muhaddithin (Hadith scholars),
~~Hadith Hasan is also reliable as Hadith Sahih.
