### ||| AUTO 47 - وعن معاذ بن جبل رضي الله عنه أن النبي صلى الله عليه
~~وسلم قال : [ من كظم غيظا وهو قادر على أن ينفذه دعاه الله سبحانه على رؤوس
~~الخلائق يوم القيامة حتى يخيره من الحور العين ما شاء ] رواه أبو داود
~~والترمذي وقال حديث حسن.
# . 47- Mu`adh bin Anas (May Allah be pleased with him) reported: The
~~Prophet (PBUH) said, "The one who suppresses anger and has the power to
~~give effect to it, will be called out by Allah, the Exalted, to the
~~forefront of the creatures on the Day of Resurrection and he will be
~~asked to choose any of the virgins (Hur) of his liking".
# [Abu Dawud and At-Tirmidhi].
# Commentary: The word `Hur' is the plural of `Haura', an extremely
~~beautiful woman of fair complexion. The word "Ein" is the plural of
~~"Aina", woman with large eyes. Both the words stand for the most
~~beautiful women who will be awarded to Muslims in Jannah. This Hadith
~~mentions the distinction and reward of self-control of a man who, in
~~spite of being powerful and having the means to avenge, suppresses his
~~rage and does not exercise his power.
