### ||| AUTO 48 - وعن أبي هريرة رضي الله عنه أن رجلا قال للنبي صلى الله
~~عليه وسلم أوصني . قال :
# [ لا تغضب ] فردد مرارا قال : [ لا تغضب ] رواه البخاري.
# . 48- Abu Hurairah (May Allah be pleased with him) reported: A man
~~asked the Prophet (PBUH) for an advice and he (PBUH) said, "Do not get
~~angry". The man repeated that several times and he replied, "Do not get
~~angry".
# [Al-Bukhari].
# Commentary:
# . 1- Rage which is declared objectionable is the one which concerns
~~worldly affairs but that which is for Allah and His religion, that is to
~~say, which occurs on the violation of the Injunctions of Allah, is
~~meritorious and essential.
# . 2- Anyone who gets furious quickly should be advised again and again
~~to control his anger so that he becomes conscious of this weakness and
~~tries to overcome it.
# . 3- Rage is a means of fulfillment of satanic aims; so it is a great
~~evil and people are advised to make every effort to prevent themselves
~~from this satanic device.
