~~of Allah (PBUH) said, "A Muslim, male or female, continues to remain
~~under trial in respect of his life, property and offspring until he
~~faces Allah, the Exalted, with no sin record".
# [At-Tirmidhi].
# Commentary: We come to know from this Hadith that Muslims are special
~~targets of trials, but a redeeming feature of these trials is that
~~Muslims' sins are pardoned through them provided they remain firm in
~~their Faith and patience.
