~~Pilgrimage was the last pilgrimage, the Prophet (PBUH) performed, and on
~~this occasion he bade farewell to the people and for this reason it came
~~to be known as Hajjat-ul-Wada`. Obedience of the rulers is stressed but
~~it is conditional, that is to say, they are to be obeyed only if their
~~orders are not against the injunctions of Allah. Similarly, their
~~obedience is obligatory till such time that they do not do anything
~~which amounts to open disbelief. If any of these two things occurs, then
~~no obedience would be due to them.
