### ||| AUTO 89 - الثالث عن جابر رضي الله عنه قال قال رجل للنبي صلى الله
~~عليه وسلم يوم أحد : أرأيت إن قتلت فأين أنا ؟ قال : [ في الجنة ] فألقى
~~تمرات كن في يده ثم قاتل حتى قتل . متفق عليه
# 89. Jabir (May Allah be pleased with him) reported: A man, said to the
~~Prophet (PBUH) during the battle of Uhud: "Tell me where I shall be if I
~~am killed". When he (PBUH) replied that he would be in Jannah, the man
~~threw away some dates which he had in his hand and fought until he was
~~killed.
# [Al-Bukhari and Muslim].
# Commentary: This Hadith mentions the passion of the Companions of the
~~Prophet (PBUH) for Jihad and its reward which is Jannah. It also says
~~that if a person heartily desires martyrdom, Allah certainly grants him
~~this distinction and honour.
