~~of Allah (PBUH) said. "The (Hell) Fire is surrounded with all kinds of
~~desires and passions, while Jannah is surrounded with adversities.''
# [Al-Bukhari and Muslim].
# Commentary: The way to Hell is littered with these evils. When a
~~person crosses them, it is an indication that he has entered into Hell.
~~On the other side exists a series of griefs and calamities, Islamic
~~injunctions and obligations (the compliance with which is often irksome
~~for man) impede his way to Jannah. When a person endures them with
~~patience he, in fact, overcomes those obstacles and becomes eligible for
~~Jannah.
