# 135. Jabir (May Allah be pleased with him) reported: Messenger of
~~Allah (PBUH) said, "When a Muslim plants a tree, whatever is eaten from
~~it is charity from him and whatever is stolen is charity and whatever is
~~subtracted from it is charity".
# [Muslim].
# Another narration says: "If a Muslim plants a tree, or sows a field
~~and men and beasts and birds eat from it, all of it is charity from him".
# Commentary: This Hadith highlights the importance of gardening and
~~agriculture. It is also one of the merits of these two occupations that
~~if someone patiently bears the loss that he suffers due to pilferage or
~~theft of their produce, he is rewarded for it.
