~~like so-and-so. He used to get up at night for optional prayer but
~~abandoned it later.''
# [Al-Bukhari and Muslim].
# Commentary: The excellence of manners demands that if someone has
~~something reprehensible in his character, the person concerned should
~~not be mentioned but the shortcoming must be indicated so that people
~~refrain from it. The second point that we learn from this Hadith is that
~~if one starts a good deed, he should try his best to do it perpetually
~~because its perpetuation is liked by Allah.
