# 159. Salamah bin Al-Akwa` (May Allah be pleased with him) reported: My
~~father said that a person ate in the presence of Messenger of Allah
~~(PBUH) with his left hand. He (PBUH) said, "Eat with your right hand".
~~He said, "I cannot do that.'' Thereupon he (the Prophet) said, "May you
~~never do that.'' It was pride that prevented him from doing it. And he
~~could not raise it (the right hand) up to his mouth afterwards.
# [Muslim].
# Commentary:
