# 172. Ibn Mas`ud (May Allah be pleased with him) reported: The Prophet
~~(PBUH) said, "The first son of Adam* takes a share of the guilt of every
~~one who murders another wrongfully because he was the initiator of
~~committing murder".
# [Al-Bukhari and Muslim].
# * The son of Adam in the Hadith is said to be Qabil. Allah tells us
~~about his story in Surat Al-Ma'idah (The Table spread with Food). Verses 27-31.
# Commentary: This Hadith gives us an idea how serious is the crime of
~~initiating an evil which is followed by others. One who initiates an
~~evil would be sinful for all those who follow him in that crime till the
~~Day of Resurrection. The safest course, therefore, is that one should
~~abstain from heresy and stick to obedience only.
