# Commentary: We learn from this Hadith that the consequences of
~~committing acts which are forbidden in Islam are not confined only to
~~those persons who commit them, but the whole society has to suffer for
~~them. It is, therefore, essential that the people who are in the habit
~~of committing sinful acts and violate Divine injunctions, should be
~~checked to save the whole society from destruction. If this is not done,
~~the entire society will have to face the Divine punishment.
