~~Allah (PBUH) said, "A believer continues to guard his Faith (and thus
~~hopes for Allah's Mercy) so long as he does not shed blood unjustly".
# [Al-Bukhari].
# Commentary: This Hadith has two meanings. Firstly, so long as a Muslim
~~does not kill another Muslim without valid reason, he remains, by the
~~Grace of Allah, capable of acting upon the Deen. That is to say, he is
~~more hopeful of the Mercy of Allah, and deserves it also, as long as he
~~does not commit murder. When he kills an innocent person, the gate of
~~Allah's Compassion is closed on him.
# Ibn Al-Arabi interpretted this Hadith as follows:
# A Muslim will still have ample chance for accomplishing good deeds to
~~face evil deeds until he sheds blood. Or, he has the chance of
~~forgiveness until he sheds blood. (M.R.M.)
