# 230. `Aishah (May Allah bepleased with her) reported: The Prophet
~~(PBUH) prohibited his Companions out of mercy for them, from observing
~~continuous fasting without a break. They said: "But you observe fast
~~continuously". He replied, "I am not like you. I spend the night while
~~my Rubb provides me with food and drink".
# [Al-Bukhari and Muslim].
# (This means that Allah has bestowed upon him the power of endurance
~~like that of a person who eats and drinks).
# Commentary: The words "I am not like you'' should not be taken to mean
~~here: "I am not a human like you''. What they really mean is that no one
~~else has that special contact with Allah which he has. On account of
~~this quality which was special to the Prophet (PBUH), it is prohibited
~~to keep fast continuously. In fact it is not only prohibited, but
~~unlawful. In such cases, it is obligatory for Muslims to follow him
~~faithfully.
