# 287. Mu`adh bin Jabal (May Allah be pleased with him) reported: The
~~Prophet (PBUH) said, "Whenever a woman harms her husband in this world
~~(that is without any due right), his wife among the (Houris in Jannah)
~~says: `You must not harm him. May Allah destroy you! He is only a
~~passing guest with you and is about to leave you to come to us".
# [At-Tirmidhi].
# Commentary: The Islamic Shari`ah commands men to treat their wives
~~with kindness. In the same spirit it commands wives to be obedient to
~~their husbands. She can hurt the feelings of her husband by using
~~indecent language, immodest conduct, immoral actions and making unfair
~~demands which are beyond his means. It is very common among women to
~~tease and trouble their husbands by these three practices, except for
~~pious women.
