### ||| AUTO 289 - وعن أبي هريرة رضي الله عنه قال قال رسول الله صلى الله
~~عليه وسلم : [ دينار أنفقته في سبيل الله ودينار أنفقته في رقبة ودينار
~~تصدقت به على مسكين ودينار أنفقته على أهلك أعظمها أجرا الذي أنفقته على
~~أهلك ] رواه مسلم
# 289. Abu Hurairah (May Allah be pleased with him) reported: Messenger
~~of Allah (PBUH) said, "A dinar you spend in Allah's way, or to free a
~~slave, or as a charity you give to a needy person, or to support your
~~family, the one yielding the greatest reward is that which you spend on
~~your family".
# [Muslim].
# Commentary: A Muslim is ordained to spend first of all on the need of
~~his wife and children and their food and clothes. There is greater
~~reward for him in this because these expenses are obligatory on him
~~while spending on other items is in the nature of Nawafil. Obviously,
~~one cannot forego the former for the latter.
PageV01P362
