~~Prophet (PBUH) said, "When someone spends on his family seeking his
~~reward for it from Allah, it is counted as a charity from him".
# [Al-Bukhari and Muslim].
# Commentary: `Seeking his reward' means that one is supporting his
~~family as a duty entrusted by Allah. It is also warranted by compassion
~~for the near ones. A person who does it as a duty ordained by Allah and
~~shows mercy to his deserving relatives to attain His Pleasure then what
~~he spends with this intention on his children will be eligible for
~~reward from Allah.
