# 356. Maimun bin Abu Shabib (May Allah had mercy upon him) reported: A
~~begger asked `Aishah (May Allah be pleased with her) for charity and she
~~gave him a piece of bread. Thereafter, one well-dressed person asked her
~~for charity and she invited him to sit down and served him food. When
~~she was asked about the reason for the difference in treatment, she
~~said: "Messenger of Allah (PBUH) instructed us: `Treat people according
~~to their status".
# [Abu Dawud].
# Commentary: This Hadith stresses that:
# 1. One should neither belittle a respectable person nor should one
~~elevate a mean one. Everyone should be treated according to his real
~~status.
# 2. It is unbecoming to take support from the Qur'an and Hadith and
~~twist it to substantiate one's own views.
# 3. The Hadith, however, is classified as Da`if (weak) as there is no
~~link in the chain of its narrators between `Aishah and Maimun.
