~~pleased with him) remained with the Prophet's mother, Aminah, and took
~~great care in his upbringing. Subsequently, the Prophet (PBUH) set her
~~free and then she was married to Zaid bin Harithah (May Allah be pleased
~~with her) This Hadith holds justification for weeping over the death of
~~the pious and also shows that it is desirable to visit such persons to
~~whom one's friends go to pay respect. The incident mentioned in this
~~Hadith also shows the love that the Companions of the Prophet (PBUH) had
