~~wrote) `My Mercy surpasses My Wrath".
# Commentary: Imam Al-Khattabi states that here the word "Kitab''
~~(translated here as `Book') means the decision of Almighty Allah which
~~He has already made, an instance of which is the following Verse of the
~~Noble Qur'an:
# "Allah has decreed: `Verily, it is I and My Messengers who shall be
~~the victorious". (58:21).
# In this Ayah the Arabic word "Kataba'' is used in the sense of "Qada'
~~(decided);'' or the word "Kataba'' signifies "Lauh Mahfooz'' on which He
~~has recorded everything. Almighty Allah is on the 'Arsh' (the Throne of
~~Allah) and this Book is with Him. (Fath Al-Bari, Kitab At-Tauhid, Bab:
~~Wa kana Arshuhu `alal-Ma'.)
