# 442. Anas (May Allah be pleased with him) reported: Messenger of Allah
~~(PBUH) said, "Allah, the Exalted, has said: `O son of adam, I forgive
~~you as long as you pray to Me and hope for My forgiveness, whatever sins
~~you have committed. O son of 'Adam, I do not care if your sins reach the
~~height of the heaven, then you ask for my forgiveness, I would forgive
~~you. O son of 'Adam, if you come to Me with an earth load of sins, and
~~meet Me associating nothing to Me, I would match it with an earthload of
