# [At-Tirmidhi].
# Commentary:
# 1. What it really means is that if sins of a Muslim, committed in
~~ignorance and carelessness, become so numerous that in stacks touch the
~~heights of skies, he should not lose hope in Allah's Mercy. If he
~~repents wholeheartedly for his sins, makes penitence for them and begs
~~Allah's forgiveness, he will certainly find Allah's Mercy open for him.
# 2. Shirk (polytheism) is an absolutely unpardonable sin. All other
~~sins, how many and how grave they may be, can be forgiven by Allah. He
~~will pardon them if He likes and send the sinful persons straight to
~~Jannah, or keep them for a while in Hell and then shift them to Jannah.
~~In any case, the punishment of Hell will not be eternal for them, as it
~~is for the Mushriks (polytheist).
