# [Abu Dawud].
# Commentary: This Hadith invites our attention to a simple way of
~~living - ordinary dress and simple and non-rich food - and discourages
~~us from being habitual of an affected life style - use of costly dress,
~~delicious and rich food and other dainties of life. The more a man shuns
~~the trappings and accessories of life, the better engaged will he be in
~~being readied for the Hereafter. The increased degree of his involvement
~~in worldly comforts and luxuries will keep decreasing his concern for
~~the accountability of future life. We may keep it in mind that
~~simplicity does not mean escape from cleanliness. Because cleanliness is
~~in itself `half the Faith'. How can a believer ignore purity and
~~cleanliness?
