# [ المزعة ] بضم الميم وإسكان الزاي وبالعين المهملة : القطعة
# 530. Ibn `Umar (May Allah be pleased with them) reported: The Prophet
~~(PBUH) said, "If one of you would keep begging (of people) until he
~~meets Allah (on the Day of Resurrection) his face will be without a
~~shred of flesh.''
# [Al-Bukhari and Muslim].
# Commentary: The lack of flesh from the face is either metaphorically
~~indicative of disgrace and wretchedness, or it would factually happen as
~~a symptom of sinning and the punishment thereof. This seems to be more
~~plausible. Aversion against begging has been fomented in this Hadith
~~because it brings shame both in this world and the Hereafter
