~~Baqi`-al-Gharqad.''
# [Muslim].
# Commentary: The example of Messenger of Allah (PBUH) shows that it is
~~right to visit the graves even at night. But the visitor is required to
~~pray the Prophetic prayer there as it invokes Divine blessing on and
~~pardon to the dead. It may be emphasized here that to greet the dead is
~~a prayer for them. It is not necessary that they should hear it and also
~~respond to it. Allah has the power to make them hear it, too. But ours
~~should not be the belief that the dead do hear and reply. The exact
~~position is known to Allah Alone. We are only supposed to follow the
~~example of Messenger of Allah (PBUH) and say the greeting and prayer as
~~mentioned above.
