~~Messenger of Allah (PBUH) said, "Let none of you wish for death, nor he
~~ask for it before it comes to him, because when he dies, his actions
~~will be terminated; certainly the age of a (true) believer does not add
~~but good.''
# Commentary: This Hadith forbids a believer to wish for his death as
~~the longevity of his age suits him by all means. The longer he lives,
~~the greater degree of progress will he make in virtues pursuits. And in
~~case he infringes upon the Shari`ah rules, he may perhaps incline
~~towards penitence. A believer should, therefore, consider his life as a
~~boon and try his utmost to do good things.
