### ||| AUTO 600 - وعن أبي هريرة رضي الله عنه عن النبي صلى الله عليه
~~وسلم قال : [ ما بعث الله نبيا إلا رعى الغنم ] فقال أصحابه : وأنت ؟ قال :
~~[ نعم كنت أرعاها على قراريط لأهل مكة ] رواه البخاري
# 600. Abu Hurairah (May Allah be pleased with him) reported: Messenger
~~of Allah (PBUH) said, "Every Prophet has tended sheep''. He was asked:
~~"And did you?'' He replied, "Yes, I tended them for a few carats for the
~~Makkans.''
# [Al-Bukhari].
# Commentary: The Prophet (PBUH) used to graze the sheep of Makkans for
~~a few carats (a carat is one-twentieth, or a bit more, of a dinar). This
~~practice was indeed a Divine training for the Prophets so that it might
~~be easier for them to deal with humans and forbear afflictions which
~~came to them from men. A shepherd indeed needs greater patience and
~~forbearance to look after his herd. This practice proved useful to the
~~Prophets. Moreover, this Hadith is suggestive of the adoption of a
~~lawful occupation, no matter how people may look askance at it. That was
~~the reason why the Prophets took such occupations.
