# 612. `Abdullah bin Mas`ud (May Allah be pleased with him) reported:
~~The Prophet (PBUH) said, "He who has, in his heart, an ant's weight of
~~arrogance will not enter Jannah.'' Someone said: "A man likes to wear
~~beautiful clothes and shoes?'' Messenger of Allah (PBUH) said, "Allah is
~~Beautiful, He loves beauty. Arrogance means ridiculing and rejecting the
~~Truth and despising people.''
# [Muslim].
# Commentary: The Hadith says that a man who has even an iota of pride
~~in his heart will be barred from entering Jannah. The Hadith word used
~~for the smallest amount means in Arabic either the smallest ant or the
~~particle which is radiated by sun-rays and seen through a wall-chink.
~~Obviously, such a particle has almost a non-existent amount, but even
~~this much is disapproved by Allah. If pride incites a man to deny the
~~existence of Allah and His Revelation, he is sure to be thrown into
~~Hell. He also faces Divine displeasure and the danger of infernal fire
~~if mere consideration of riches, physical beauty, social and
~~intellectual prominence and family status makes him proud and self-
~~conceited and he looks down upon others, or persists in the denial of
~~Truth. First he will receive punishment and only then will be admitted
~~into Jannah. A good dress, however, is not counted the sign of pride.
