~~view of the overall national interest, is therefore, preferable to
~~revolting against him. True, one cannot take the law into one's own
~~hands, yet there always remains room for improvement and positive
~~criticism. To make use of it within limits and to make efforts for the
~~enforcement of the canonical discipline will not be deemed as an
~~uprising. Indeed, this will be deemed, to some extent, binding on
~~everybody.
