~~Messenger of Allah (PBUH) used to speak clearly and decisively. However,
~~it may also mean that, while speaking, he would pause upon his words in
~~such a way that each and every word which came from his lips appeared
~~detached from the other. He was never like those who speak quickly and
~~their words are mixed up with each other. This Hadith reflects the
~~Prophet's eloquence as well as his due care and decency in putting in
~~his viewpoint to the convenience of his audience.
