### ||| AUTO 716 - وعن عبد الله بن يزيد الخطمي الصحابي رضي الله عنه قال
~~: كان رسول الله صلى الله عليه وسلم إذا أراد أن يودع الجيش يقول : [
~~أستودع الله دينكم وأمانتكم وخواتيم أعمالكم ] حديث صحيح رواه أبو داود
~~وغيره بإسناد صحيح
# 716. `Abdullah bin Yazid Al-Khatmi (May Allah be pleased with him)
~~reported: When Messenger of Allah (PBUH) intended to bid farewell to his
~~army he would say: "Astau-di'ullaha dinakaum, wa amanatakum, wa
~~khawatima `amalikum (I entrust Allah with your Deen, your trust and your
~~last deeds).''
# [Abu Dawud].
# Commentary: This Hadith presents the same benediction as stated above.
~~Yet, here its addresses are the plural number of second person, whereas
~~in the previous Hadith it was singular number. The Hadith points out the
~~virtue desirability of the leader to bid farewell to his army before
~~they set out for the battlefield, and to advise them using the Prophet's
~~words stated above, reminding them to hold fast to their religion for
~~which they have left everything behind to fight for it and to win
~~Allah's Mercy.
