### ||| AUTO 717 - وعن أنس رضي الله عنه قال : جاء رجل إلى النبي صلى الله
~~عليه وسلم فقال : يا رسول الله إني أريد سفرا فزودني . فقال : [ زودك الله
~~التقوى ] قال : زدني . قال : [ وغفر ذنبك ] . قال : زدني . قال : [ ويسر لك
~~الخير حيثما كنت ] رواه الترمذي وقال حديث حسن
# 717. Anas (May Allah be pleased with him) reported: A man came to the
~~Prophet (PBUH) and said: "O Messenger of Allah! I intend to go on a
~~journey, so supplicate for me.'' He (PBUH) said, "May Allah grant you
~~the provision of piety.'' The man said: "Please supplicate more for
~~me.'' He (PBUH) said, "May He forgive your sins!'' The man repeated:
~~"Please supplicate more for me.'' Messenger of Allah (PBUH) said, "May
~~He facilitate for you the doing of good wherever you are.''
# [At-Tirmidhi].
# Commentary: Spiritually speaking, the most beneficial thing that a
~~traveller can bank upon is a benediction. So, it is desirable for a
~~traveller to visit his fellow Muslim brother to pray for him before he
~~starts his journey.
