# 736. Abu Hurairah (May Allah be pleased with him) reported: Messenger
~~of Allah (PBUH) never found fault with food. If he had inclination to
~~eating it, he would eat; and if he disliked it, he would leave it.
# Al-Bukhari and Muslim].
# Commentary: This Hadith throws light on the Prophet's excellent
~~manners which ought to be followed by all Muslims. It is a deplorable
~~state of affairs that when we find a dish a bit unsavoury, we lose our
~~temper and create quite a scene in the house. May we follow the
~~excellent example of our Prophet (PBUH)!
