# 740. `Umar bin Abu Salamah (May Allah be pleased with them) reported:
~~I was a boy under the care of Messenger of Allah (PBUH), and as my hand
~~used to wander around in the dish, he (PBUH) said to me once, "Mention
~~Allah's Name (i.e., say Bismillah), eat with your right hand, and eat
~~from what is in front of you.''
# [Al-Bukhari and Muslim].
# Commentary: `Umar bin Abu Salamah (May Allah be pleased with them) had
~~learnt table manners from Messenger of Allah (PBUH) who was his
~~stepfather and guardian. Hence, everybody is morally bound to teach his
~~wards or children good manners.
