### ||| AUTO 803 - عن عمرو بن شعيب عن أبيه عن جده رضي الله عنه قال قال
~~رسول الله صلى الله عليه وسلم : [ إن الله يحب أن يرى أثر نعمته على عبده ]
~~رواه الترمذي وقال حديث حسن
# 803. `Amr bin Shu`aib on the authority of his father and grandfather
~~reported: Messenger of Allah (PBUH) said, "Allah loves to see the sign
~~of His Bounties on his slave.''
# [At-Tirmidhi].
# Commentary: A simple dress is commendable if one wears it as a gesture
~~of humility wining Allah's Pleasure. Yet, to zealously pursue the goal
~~of goodness, to extend a helping hand to the indigent and the needy, to
~~behave favourably towards one's relatives and to wear a fine dress as a
~~manifestation of Allah's Favours are equally good acts of high merit. A
~~fine dress is not impeachable in itself but it becomes so, if worn with
~~an air of arrogance and self-importance. On the other hand, an
~~expression of Divine bounty makes it praiseworthy. In other words, it is
~~the intention which makes an act good or bad. Alongside the practice of
~~the example of Messenger of Allah (PBUH), the sincerity of action and
~~making right intention, therefore, become indispensable.
