~~acts of disobedience; and such obedience as will take us to Your Jannah;
~~and such as will make easy for us to bear in the calamities of this
~~world. O Allah! let us enjoy our hearing, our sight and our power as
~~long as You keep us alive and make our heirs from our own offspring, and
~~make our revenge restricted to those who oppress us, and support us
~~against those who are hostile to us let no misfortune afflict our Deen;
~~let not worldly affairs be our principal concern, or the ultimate limit
~~of our knowledge, and let not those rule over us who do not show mercy
~~to us).''
# [At-Tirmidhi].
# Commentary: This Hadith reveals a prayer through which we may be able
~~to reach all that which is good in this world as well as in the
~~Hereafter.
