~~Indeed, a believer never utters anything out of malice or self-conceit.
~~There are some Ahadith which forbid us to speak ill of dead people. This
~~rule applies to the true believers only. The Shari`ah argument is
~~against it. However, we are allowed to talk about the misdeeds of the
~~infidels and people who commit sins openly, disregarding the Shari`ah so
~~that others may abstain from imitating a bad example.
