# 958. Ibn `Umar (May Allah be pleased with them) reported: The
~~Messenger of Allah (PBUH) said, "Were people to know of what I know
~~about the dangers of travelling alone, no rider would travel alone at
~~night.''
# [Al-Bukhari].
# Commentary: Lonely travelling, whatever its form, is inadvisable at
~~night and can cause many inconveniences. These inconveniences include
~~deprivation of performing congregational prayers, feelings of loneliness
~~and isolation and facing unexpected situations and damages. But the real
~~reasons behind this prohibition, only Allah knows.
