# [At-Tirmidhi and Abu Dawud].
# Commentary: An army of twelve thousand soldiers, if endowed with
~~strong faith and resolve, is enough to face even an army of large size.
~~It cannot be defeated merely on the basis of number. Some other factors
~~accounting for its defeat may not be ruled out, but it will not be
~~overpowered for its small number.
