### ||| AUTO 966 - وعن سهل بن عمرو . وقيل : سهل بن الربيع بن عمرو
~~الأنصاري المعروف بابن الحنظلية وهو من أهل بيعة الرضوان رضي الله عنهم قال
~~: مر رسول الله صلى الله عليه وسلم ببعير قد لحق ظهره ببطنه فقال : [ اتقوا
~~الله في هذه البهائم المعجمة فاركبوها صالحة وكلوها صالحة ] رواه أبو داود
~~بإسناد صحيح
# 966. Sahl bin `Amr known as Ibn Al-Hanzaliyyah reported: The Messenger
~~of Allah (PBUH) happened to pass by a camel whose belly was sticking to
~~its back (because of hunger), whereupon he said, "Fear Allah in respect
~~of these dumb (animals). Ride them while they are fit, and slaughter
~~them and eat their meat when they are fit.''
# [Abu Dawud].
# Commentary: This Hadith lays emphasis on taking care of animals.
~~Because if they are hungry or you overload them, they will not be able
~~to speak out their suffering to you in human language. You are,
~~therefore, supposed to take care of their food and other requirements by
~~yourself. In case you fail in your duty to them, Allah will take you to
~~task. Moreover, eating the flesh of sick and lean animals is unhygienic
~~and can endanger health. Whereas, the flesh of a healthy and robust
~~animal gives energy and strength to human body.
PageV01P1246
### ||| AUTO 967 - وعن أبي جعفر عبد الله بن جعفر رضي الله عنه قال :
