# 973. `Abdullah bin Sarjis (May Allah be pleased with him) reported:
~~Whenever the Messenger of Allah (PBUH) proceeded on a journey, he would
~~seek refuge in Allah from the hardships of the journey, and against
~~deviation after guidance, and against the supplication of the oppressed,
~~and occurrences of unpleasant events in the family and property. He
~~would say: "Allahumma inni a`udhu bika min wa`tha'is-safari, wa
~~kaabatil-munqalabi, wal-hauri ba`dal-kauni, wa da`watil-mazlumi, wa su
~~'il-manzari fil-ahli wal-mal.''
# [Muslim].
# Commentary: The Prophet (PBUH) sought Divine refuge against the
~~supplication of the oppressed because Allah immediately responds to it.
~~It is, therefore, imperative that if a man has wronged anybody, he
~~should recompense his wrongdoing before embarking on a journey because
~~the malediction of the wronged may invoke Divine wrath exposing the
~~wrongdoer to a risky and troublesome journey.
