# 980. Abu Hurairah (May Allah be pleased with him) reported: The
~~Messenger of Allah (PBUH) said, "Three supplications are answered
~~without doubt. The supplication of the oppressed, the supplication of
~~the traveller, and the supplication of the parent for his son.''
# [At-Tirmidhi and Abu Dawud].
# Commentary: This Hadith mentions two dimensions of supplications.
~~First, the supplication of an oppressed person will be in favour of the
~~one who will come to his help and redress his complaint, whereas the
~~oppressor will be hit by his supplication. Second, Allah also answers
~~the father's supplication for his disobedient and impudent son; and the
~~mother's supplication is even more effective than that of the father's
~~because, as compared to him, she has more rights over them. Man should,
~~therefore, restrain himself from disobeying parents, so that he may
~~escape in both cases the supplication which is not rejected by Allah.
