# 1053. Abu Hurairah (May Allah be pleased with him) reported: The
~~Messenger of Allah (PBUH) said, "He who goes to the mosque in the
~~morning or in the evening, Allah prepares for him a place in Jannah
~~whenever he goes to the mosque in the morning and returns from it in the
~~evening.''
# [Al-Bukhari and Muslim].
# Commentary: This Hadith points out the merit of going on foot to the
~~mosque for Salat, no matter whether one goes in the morning or the
~~evening. In fact, the heart of a Muslim should be attached to mosques
~~and on account of this, he goes there at all the prescribed hours of
~~Salat to perform his Salat in congregation.
