~~Messenger of Allah (PBUH) said, "When anyone of you has performed two of
~~Sunnah before the Fajr prayer, he should lie down on his right side."
# [Abu Dawud and At-Tirmidhi].
# Commentary: The preceding Ahadith described the practice of the
~~Prophet (PBUH) while the present one tells us about his order that one
~~should lie down on his right side after offering the two Sunnah of Fajr
~~prayer. Thus, this practice is proved by his speech as well as action
~~which does not leave any doubt about it being a Sunnah and Mustahabb
~~(desirable).
