# 1153. Samurah (May Allah be pleased with him) reported: The Messenger
~~of Allah (PBUH) said, "It suffices to perform Wudu' properly for the
~~Friday prayer; but it is better to take a bath.''
# [Abu Dawud and At-Tirmidhi].
# Commentary: This Hadith supports the contention of those who do not
~~hold the Ghusl obligatory for two reasons. Firstly, it allows one to
~~perform Wudu'. In fact, it has been regarded good. Secondly, the Ghusl
~~has been regarded better, from which one can safely infer the permission
~~to leave it. In any case, there is no doubt about its being Masnun
~~(Sunnah of the Prophet (PBUH)) and Mustahabb (desirable). The time of
~~the Ghusl is from the daybreak to the time of Salat-ul-Jumu`ah.
