~~(PBUH) performed the night prayer in pairs (i.e., Rak`ah) and made it
~~odd number by observing one Rak`ah (as Witr).
# [Al-Bukhari and Muslim].
# Commentary: Both the foregoing Ahadith tell us that the Nafl Salat
~~performed at night should be in the form of couplets followed by one
~~Rak`ah of Witr. Thus, this Hadith not only brings out justification for
~~one Rak`ah Witr but also proves its superiority. Even if one has to
~~perform three Rak`ah Witr, he should first perform two and then perform
~~one separately.
