~~(PBUH) to sleep on his right side after performing two Sunnah of Fajr
~~prayer. It also tells us that he used to make long prostrations in
~~Tahajjud prayer, because one gets closer to Allah in a state of
~~prostration. This Hadith also stresses on utmost concentration in Salat
~~as it is highly pleasing to Allah and there is a greater possibility of
~~acceptance of prayer which is made in a state of prostration.
