~~(PBUH) would sleep during the early part of night and stand in Salat
~~during the latter part.
# [Al-Bukhari and Muslim].
# Commentary: This Hadith tells us about the ordinary routine of the
~~Prophet (PBUH). Ordinarily, he would go to sleep in the first part of
~~the night and perform Tahajjud prayer in the later portion, which is the
~~best time for it. But, as already mentioned in the preceding Ahadith, he
~~sometimes also performed it in the early as well as middle hours of the night.
