# 1182. `Umar bin Al-Khattab (May Allah be pleased with him) reported:
~~The Messenger of Allah (PBUH) said: "If anyone falls asleep and
~~therefore fails to observe his Hizb (share) or part of it, if he
~~observes it between the Fajr and the Zuhr prayers, it will be recorded
~~for him as though he had observed it during the night.''
# [Muslim].
# Commentary: This Hadith has already been mentioned. The word "Hizb''
~~literally means "share'' and "turn''. Here it means that (daily round of
~~recitation) which a person determines for himself, such as prayer or
~~recitation of the Qur'an. For instance, if a person decides that he will
~~perform eight Rak`ah in Tahajjud, recite one Juz` (part) of the Qur'an
~~everyday, remember Allah in such and such form for so many times etc.,
~~etc. And then he makes every possible effort to put into practice his
~~decision, but if casually he is unable to fulfill his routine, he should
~~do it afterwards. This action of his will be credited to his account by
~~Allah as if he completed it at the appointed time. This Hadith furnishes
~~justification for the performance of optional righteous acts even after
~~their due time.
