# [Al-Bukhari].
# Commentary: We learn from this Hadith that Lailat-ul-Qadr occurs in
~~any of the five odd nights - 21st, 23rd, 25th, 27th and 29th - of the
~~last ten nights of Ramadan. Its exact date has not been revealed for the
~~reason that people keep themselves awake for prayer for a larger number
~~of nights. Had its date been fixed, people would have kept awake for
~~prayer only on that night. There is a general belief among the scholars
~~that it is fixed, on the 27th night of Ramadan. But this is not correct.
~~Ahadith do not confirm this view.
