### ||| AUTO 1194 - وعنها رضي الله عنها قالت : كان رسول الله صلى الله
~~عليه وسلم يجتهد في رمضان ما لا يجتهد في غيره وفي العشر الأواخر منه ما لا
~~يجتهد في غيره . رواه مسلم
# 1194. `Aishah (May Allah be pleased with her) reported: The Messenger
~~of Allah (PBUH) used to strive more in worship during Ramadan than he
~~strove in any other time of the year; and he would devote himself more
~~(in the worship of Allah) in the last ten nights of Ramadan than he
~~strove in earlier part of the month.
# [Muslim].
# Commentary: We learn from this Hadith that:
# 1. One should concentrate more on prayers and worship on the last ten
~~nights of Ramadan than the first twenty nights, in the same way as one
~~should do more worship in Ramadan than in the other months.
# 2. One should keep oneself awake for prayer, worship and glorification
~~of Allah in the last ten nights of Ramadan so that one can attain the
~~blessings of Lailat-ul-Qadr.
# 3. One should also persuade his family members to keep themselves
~~awake for prayer and worship in the last ten odd nights of Ramadan so
~~that they can also make efforts to please Allah.
# 4. I`tikaf (seclusion in the mosque for prayers) in the last ten days
~~of Ramadan is also a meritorious act for its being a practice of the
~~Prophet (PBUH).
