~~exert myself in weeping for him.'' He (PBUH) replied, "O mother of
~~Harithah, in in the gardens of Jannah there are many ranks, and your son
~~has attained Al-Firdaus, the highest.''
# [Al-Bukhari].
# Commentary: Jannat-ul-Firdaus is the highest portion of Jannah. The
~~allocation of this portion to the martyrs is a proof that Jihad is very
~~much liked by Allah. It occurs in Ahadith that when someone prays to
~~Allah, he should always pray for Jannat-ul-Firdaus.
