~~of the swords.'' Then he (PBUH) said: "Allahumma munzilal-kitab, wa
~~mujriyas-sahab, wa hazimal-Ahzab, ihzimhum wansurna alaihim (O Allah,
~~Revealer of the Book, Disperser of the clouds, Defeater of the
~~Confederates, put our enemy to rout and support us against them).''
# [Al-Bukhari and Muslim].
# Commentary:
# 1. This Hadith has already been mentioned, and we learn from it that
~~it is better to start war in the afternoon because this was the practice
~~of the Prophet (PBUH).
# 2. The desire for war is prohibited, but when war becomes inevitable,
~~one should not show his back to the enemy; rather, one should fight to
~~the best of his ability and be steadfast in it.
# 3. Along with steadfastness and patience in fighting, one should also
~~pray for victory because all powers lie with Allah and no one can gain
~~victory without His Will.
# The Hadith also mentions a supplication which one should make when he
~~encounters the enemy.
