~~Messenger of Allah (PBUH) said, "When your servant brings food for you
~~and you do not seat him with you, you should at least give him a morsel
~~or two out of it because he has prepared it himself.''
# [Al-Bukhari].
# Commentary: The sense of equality of people inculcated by Islam
~~warrants that if a servant brings meal to his master, this latter should
~~make him sit by his side to take the meal with him. If this is not
~~possible for a reason or another, then he should give some portion of
~~the meal to the servant. He must not eat up the whole meal himself or
~~leave for him only the leftovers. Alas! we should adopt the teachings of
~~our religion.
