~~the number of those He will create).' Then say: `Allahu Akbar' (Allah is
~~Greatest) in the same way. Then say: `Al-hamdu lillah' (praise be to
~~Allah) in the same way. Then say: `La ilaha illallah' (there is no true
~~god except Allah) in the same way. Then say: `La hawla wa la quwwata
~~illa billah' (there is no change of a condition nor power except by
~~Allah) in the same manner.''
# [At-Tirmidhi].
# Commentary: Sheikh Al-Albani has accepted this Hadith as Hasan because
~~of the defect in its authority. He has stated that the original
~~narration of it is without any reference to gravels and stones (of
~~fruits) and that is "Sahih'' and has been mentioned by Imam Muslim in
~~his Sahih with reference to Jawairiyah (May Allah be pleased with her).
~~(See Riyad-us-Saliheen, edited by Sheikh Al-Albani).
