# 1556. Abud-Darda' (May Allah be pleased with him) said: The Messenger
~~of Allah (PBUH) said, "When a person curses somebody or something, the
~~curse goes up to heaven and the gates of heaven get closed. Then it
~~comes down to the earth and its gates get closed. Then it turns right
~~and left, and if it does not find an entrance to go anywhere, it returns
~~to the person or thing that was cursed; if he or it deserves to be
~~cursed; otherwise it returns to the person who uttered it.''
# [Abu Dawud].
# Commentary: Al-La`nah (curse) means deprivation of Allah's Mercy. We
~~learn from this Hadith that the act of cursing is such that one who does
~~it can become himself a victim of it. One should, therefore, abstain
~~from cursing.
