~~so.'' He (PBUH) said, "None can chastise with fire except the Rubb of
~~the fire.''
# [Abu Dawud].
# Commentary:
# 1. To catch nestlings of a bird and torment them or to burn the holes
~~of insects along with their inmates is forbidden. One can, however, burn
~~their vacant holes.
# 2. If somebody has burnt a person to death, it is not permissible to
~~kill him in return by burning. If the heirs of the victim want to kill
~~him in the same way under Al-Qisas (the law of equality in punishment)
~~they can do so; otherwise he can be put to the sword.
