~~the fire before going to bed, no matter whether this fire is in the form
~~of a lamp, a fireplace, or a heater. Experience shows that leaving the
~~fire alive sometime proves very dangerous. Leaving the utensils, water-
~~skins, pitchers etc., uncovered must also be avoided to prevent them
~~from dirt and insects which can cause harm. Similarly, doors and windows
~~should also be kept closed while one is sleeping in order to guard the
~~house against thieves and robbers.
# 2. One must recite the Name of Allah, that is to say Bismillah, before
~~using and keeping things.
