# 1678. Ibn `Umar (May Allah be pleased with them) said: The Messenger
~~of Allah (PBUH) said, "Those who draw pictures will be punished on the
~~Day of Resurrection; and it will be said to them: `Breathe soul into
~~what you have created.'''
# [Al-Bukhari and Muslim].
# Commentary: We learn from this Hadith that drawing pictures of humans,
~~animals and all those things that have a soul in them is a great sin and
~~is liable to heavy punishment. However, one will not be taken to task
~~for such pictures which are made compulsory by the Government, i.e.,
~~identity cards, passports, domicile certificates etc., because one
~~cannot exercise his own will in such matters, but this exemption is
~~subject to the condition that he does not exceed the compulsory
~~requirement.
