~~Allah (PBUH) said, "He who swears by Amanah (trust) is not one of us.''
# [Abu Dawud with authentic Isnad].
# Commentary: The oath of Amanah means to say "By Amanah'' as one says
~~"By Allah''. This is prohibited for the reason that one can take the
~~oath of Allah or any of His Attributes. Amanah is one of the
~~Commandments of Allah and an obligation prescribed by Him, like Salat,
~~Saum, Hajj etc. In this way, the Commandments of Allah assume the
~~resemblance of His Glorious Names and Attributes, which is not correct.
