# [At-Tirmidhi].
# [Some `Ulama' are of the opinion that the words of the Prophet (PBUH)
~~that "He who swears by anyone or anything other than Allah has indeed
~~committed an act of Kufr or Shirk,'' are in the nature of extreme
~~admonition. And in fact, it is not Shirk. The same applies to the saying
~~of the Prophet (PBUH), who said, "showing off is Shirk.'']
# Commentary: Imam An-Nawawi has regarded the saying "showing off is
~~Shirk'' as Hadith is not narrated in these words. It is, however, true
~~that what the Prophet (PBUH) has stated about the evil and sinfulness of
~~showing off implies that it is also a (minor) Shirk. For instance he
~~stated that "He who kept fast or offered Salat for mere show, has indeed
~~committed Shirk.'' In any case, to take oath of anyone other than Allah
~~is strictly forbidden. It is, therefore, necessary to abstain from
~~swearing by other than Allah. Unfortunately, such oaths are very common
~~and people do not realize that they are prohibited and unlawful.
