### ||| AUTO 1754 - عن أنس بن مالك رضي الله عنه قال قال رسول الله صلى
~~الله عليه وسلم : [ ما بال أقوام يرفعون أبصارهم إلى السماء في صلاتهم ]
~~فاشتد قوله في ذلك حتى قال : [ لينتهن عن ذلك أو لتخطفن أبصارهم ] رواه
~~البخاري
# 1754. Anas bin Malik (May Allah be pleased with him) said: The
~~Messenger of Allah (PBUH) said, "How is it that some people raise their
~~eyes towards the sky during As-Salat (the prayer)?'' He stressed (this
~~point) and added, "People must refrain from raising their eyes towards
~~heaven in Salat (prayer), or else their sights will certainly be
~~snatched away.''
# [Al-Bukhari].
# Commentary: Looking towards the sky during prayer disturbs the
~~concentration in Salat and there is a stern warning against this bad
~~habit. One can, however, do so after Salat, i.e., during one's
~~supplications.
PageV01P2285
