~~Arabia. To take oath or swear by them or by anything else besides Allah
~~is an act of disbelief which takes one out of the fold of religion.
# If any person swears by anything or anybody else other than Allah, he
~~should recite "La ilaha illa Allah" and refresh and re-establish his
~~belief in Allah. Similarly, if someone indulges in other sins, then he
~~should repent and give in charity according to his resources. The reason
~~is, as Allah (SWT) says: "Verily, the good deeds remove the evil deeds
~~(i.e., small sins).'' (11:114).
